ðŸ§® Example Code: Fraud Model Evaluation
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, roc_auc_score

y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
print("ROC-AUC:", roc_auc_score(y_test, model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]))

ðŸ“Š Key Insights

âœ… Fraud Model

Transaction velocity (number of transactions per hour) and unusual merchant location were top predictors

Model achieved ~92% ROC-AUC, reducing false negatives significantly

Helps financial institutions block high-risk payments without impacting good users

âœ… Loan Default Model

Created credit risk score from income, debt ratio, payment history

Identified high-risk borrowers ~85% accurately

Enables smarter loan approvals and interest-rate adjustments

âœ… Business Impact

âœ” Reduces chargebacks and losses from fraudulent payments
âœ” Supports smarter lending decisions and healthier loan portfolios
âœ” Improves compliance and risk monitoring processes
âœ” Enables automated, real-time scoring for finance systems

